    "inject_data": {
        "Inject 1: OSINT": {
            "desc": "\"Time to complete: 30 min \n\nWe have been notified that a hacker has been infiltrating our systems.\nThe files can be downloaded using the link: https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1AmuN76nsmlZKCI0rTdijs1URXzzkCpV1?usp=drive_link \n\nWe need to investigate the image1.jpg and image2.jpg files to figure out what is going on.\nBe sure to use Google Earth to Figure out the latitude and longitude of where these photos were taken from\n\nSubmit your findings in your team’s inject-submissions channel on Discord.\"",
            "sol": "",
            "time": "30",
            "release": "",
            "due": ""
        },
        "Inject 2: APK Investigation": {
            "desc": "\"Time to complete: 1 hr \n\nThe hacker has submitted to us a suspicious looking Android application. \nInvestigate the suspicious Homely Wallpaper_7.4.8_APKPure.apk file using jadx-gui tool and VirusTotal.\n\nVirusTotal Link: https://www.virustotal.com/gui/home/upload \n\ngit clone https://github.com/skylot/jadx.git \ncd jadx\n./gradlew dist\n\nMake sure to go to the build/jadx/bin to run the app.\n\nAPK Link: https://apkpure.com/homely-wallpaper/com.race.mely.wpaper/#google_vignette \n\nOnce you finish the analysis of suspicious details associated with the app submit your findings in your team’s inject-submissions channel on Discord. Gather as many details as possible.\"",
            "sol": "",
            "time": "60",
            "release": "",
            "due": ""
        },
        "Inject 3: Windows Malware": {
            "desc": "\"Time to complete: 1 hr\n\nGo to the url: https://www.malware-traffic-analysis.net/2025/03/10/index.html  \nDownload both zip files (located under ASSOCIATED FILES) to the Kali linux box and investigate using wireshark and Ghidra.\n\nThe zip files are password protected and use the password infected_20250310 Note, don't run any files on your system.\n\nNote: 2025-03-10-Remcos-RAT-infection-traffic.pcap.zip is where the Wireshark files are contained and 2025-03-10-email-and-malware-from-Remcos-RAT-infection.zip contains the executable file that you run through Ghidra.\n\nWarning: Under no circumstance should you run the executable or any other file you download.\n\nDownload and install the Ghydra and open the executable in Ghydra: https://github.com/NationalSecurityAgency/ghidra/releases \nRun ghidraRun file using: ./ghidraRun\n\nSubmit your findings in your team’s inject-submissions channel on Discord.\nZip File password Infected_20250310\"z",
            "sol": "",
            "time": "60",
            "release": "",
            "due": ""
        },
        "Inject 4: Network Topology": {
            "desc": "\"Time to complete: 1 hr\n\nGenerate a network topology of your infrastructure. \n\nBe sure to include your ports that are open.\nAlso be sure to map out what services you have running.\n\nDetails about network topologies can be found at: https://www.nakivo.com/blog/types-of-network-topology-explained/ \n\nNetwork Mapping Software Online: https://app.diagrams.net/ \"",
            "sol": "",
